The All Progressives Congress (APC) Presidential Campaign Council (PCC) has said that the party’s candidate, Bola Ahmed Tinubu, already has the required votes to defeat candidates of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Atiku Abubakar; Labour Party (LP), Peter Obi; and other candidates. Speaking yesterday in Abuja during a Civil Society Organisations’ (CSOs’) pre-election roundtable, the CSOs’ Director of the PCC, Senator Mohammed Hassan, said affiliate organisations were invited for the roundtable to know their level of preparation ahead of Saturday’s polls. Senator Hassan, who was represented by a member of the directorate, Comrade Okpokwu Ogenyi, said that with various briefings he had received from different organisations: “It is certain that Bola Ahmed Tinubu is the next President of Nigeria.” 